HEADWORD: Chrysarobin
<hw>Chrys`a*ro"bin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chryso`s</grk> gold + <ets>araroba</ets> a foreign name of Goa
powder + <ets>-in</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A bitter, yellow
substance forming the essential constituent of Goa powder, and yielding
chrysophanic acid proper; hence formerly called also
<altname>chrysophanic acid</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

